{
  "text": "By this lemma, it is easy to see that Corollary 5. [CITATION_1] . If x, y \u2208 T has the separation set (k 1 , . . . , k p ) = \u2205, then, by setting \u03b8 0 := x, \u03b8 p+1 := y and the choice of any angle \u03b8 i \u2208 \u0398 k i , each pair of angles \u03b8 i , \u03b8 i+1 for i \u2208 {0, . . . , p} is non-separated by \u0398.",
